    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/malaysian-style-kari-udang-king-prawn-curry-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and chop your<strong> potato[es]</strong> into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>roughly</p><p>Cut your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and slice lengthways finely \u2013 this is your <strong>julienne chilli</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/malaysian-style-kari-udang-king-prawn-curry-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>julienne chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 3-4 min or until soft</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/malaysian-style-kari-udang-king-prawn-curry-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Once the onion has softened, add your<strong> ginger & garlic paste</strong> and <strong>tamarind paste </strong>with your <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and <strong>garam masala </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/malaysian-style-kari-udang-king-prawn-curry-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>with your <strong>creamed coconut </strong>and <strong>cornflour </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/malaysian-style-kari-udang-king-prawn-curry-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chopped potato</strong>, <strong>chopped tomato</strong> and the <strong>coconut stock </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 15-18 min or until the potato is fork tender</p><p>Drain your <strong>king prawns</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/malaysian-style-kari-udang-king-prawn-curry-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potato is tender, add the <strong>drained king prawns </strong>to the pan and cook for 4-5 min or until the prawns are cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>Malaysian-style</strong> <strong>kari udang king prawn curry</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/malaysian-style-kari-udang-king-prawn-curry-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> Malaysian-style kari udang king prawn curry </strong>over the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>rice </strong>and garnish with the <strong>remaining julienne chilli </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
